"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody. I'm an old punk rocker prepper guy and well I'm a new prepper guy. I'm an old punk rock guy. And um I've always kind of been fearful of my culture, my environment, my world. I I feel like everything we're doing is unsustainable and uh that there's some real consequences that could be devastating if things crack or break or even hiccup. And so I want to grow a garden where I have a lot of food and I can prepare for something going wrong, but I it's not really the plan. If things go wrong and I have a garden, that doesn't really help me out that much. The idea is to do social media stuff and kind of inspire other people in my community, other communities, to do the gardening thing to create a trend because that's true survivalists. Survivalism isn't about individual this or individual that, stocking up guns and canned goods and having your own personal garden. No, it's about being in a community where you trust people, where everybody's relying on each other. That's where real gardening comes in if you're talking about prepping. It's not about me gardening. I can't garden enough to eat. I can't and who why wouldn't someone just come take it from me? You know? That when things get desperate, all this is tough. So the idea is to try to inspire a movement where people are doing more of the the victory garden concept from the 40s and create a community where we can trust each other, where we can sustain each other, where our big fragile supermarket system should hick up or heaven forbid, you know, kind of break. We can survive this. We can we can rely on each other, but we have to do we have to start gardening. We have to do it all over the place. This has to become a community involvement. I think it was in the 40s I'd read somewhere that during the victory garden era of World War II where they encouraged people to grow food in their backyards, seventy percent of the calories of Americans came from their gardens. It's incredible to think about. If we were to do that today, we we wouldn't get a quarter percent. Anyway, I think I'm gonna keep on doing my thing, but really it doesn't matter unless I inspire other people. This isn't really prepping until it becomes a movement. Anyway, thanks y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody.\",\n      \"start\": 0.8,\n      \"end\": 2.08,\n      \"duration\": 1.28,\n      \"confidence\": 0.979,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.8,\n          \"end\": 1.04,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.976\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 1.04,\n          \"end\": 1.2,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 1.28,\n          \"end\": 1.44,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 1.44,\n          \"end\": 1.68,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 1.68,\n          \"end\": 1.92,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \".\",\n          \"start\": 1.92,\n          \"end\": 2.08,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.901\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"text\": \" I'm an old punk rocker prepper guy and well I'm a new prepper guy.\",\n      \"start\": 2.08,\n      \"end\": 6.08,\n      \"duration\": 4.0,\n      \"confidence\": 0.994,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" I\",\n          \"start\": 2.08,\n          \"end\": 2.24,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"'\",\n          \"start\": 2.24,\n          \"end\": 2.4,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n  